# CCC-Harness — files NOT to be tracked by users' git repos
#
# This .gitignore ships with the harness and gets copied into the user's project
# at /init time. It covers the harness's transient state files.

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Transient harness state (writeable by skills at runtime)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Auditor approval JSON files (per-feature, per-stage)
# These are session-local; commit-time cleanup deletes them
.harness/state/auditor-approvals/

# Test-fixer attempt logs (per-feature)
.harness/state/test-fix/

# Auditor environment file (per-machine secrets / model overrides)
.harness/state/auditor.env

# Note: `.harness/state/install.json` is INTENTIONALLY NOT ignored.
# It's the canonical "this project is configured" marker. Teams that
# want to share harness state across collaborators should commit it.

# Audit snapshots from /audit-spec runs + auditor-gate verdict logs
# (concerns-<feature>-stage<N>-<timestamp>.json and
#  waivers-<feature>-stage<N>-<timestamp>.json, written by auditor-gate.sh
#  on CONCERNS and WAIVED verdicts respectively). These form the audit trail
#  the CEO reviews before commit; default is NOT ignored so the trail is
#  preserved. Uncomment if you want to exclude.
# .harness/audits/

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Working files that should not be committed
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Feature plan files (transient; deleted at Stage 8 commit anyway)
# If a plan file survives to commit, that's a workflow bug — but excluding
# them in .gitignore would mask the bug. Leaving uncommented for now.
# docs/features/*-plan.md

# Old-version archive directory (if user picked option 1 in bootstrap)
# Some teams may want to commit this for posterity; default: ignore
old_version_harness/

# Temp directories from installer
.ccc-harness-temp/

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Memory layer — by default tracked (cross-session, valuable for team)
# Uncomment if you prefer local-only memory:
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# .harness/memory/

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# OS / editor noise
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.swp
*.swo
*~
.idea/
.vscode/

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Optional secrets — projects often have these; leave commented as reminder
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# .env
# .env.local
# .env.*.local
